  <span id="freeText9383962355033672306" style="display:none">This was the first book I ever read about Europe just prior to the first world war. Tuchman's accessible style and choice of topics representative of the period inspired the reading of her book about the onset of the war itself, The Guns of August, immediately thereafter.<br /><br />Decades later, in 1990, I reread the thing.</span>
